<br>
It is EXTREMELY rude, careless and thoughless of others to kite mobs in the zone-in area or near graveyards.  These are not moss snakes.  These mobs hit for upwards of 500-600 points.   When people zone into a graveyard, they do not need to sit down only to have some mob love tap them for 1200 points of damage.<br>
<br>
If you need an example, the next time I catch any of you ressing in that graveyard I'm very likely to fire up a kite of my own, just to show you what low health aggro plus one of those ogres can do for your fun.<br>
<br>
There are spots in the zone that you can kill from.  Have some fucking dignity.  Pull your heads out of your overlarge asses and stop kiting in the graveyard area.  Think about others and and your own dignity and DON'T train in a zone where your XP loss is minimal with death and your corpse will be delivered to you in less than 20 minutes.<br>
<br>
You aren't playing in Crushbone anymore, kiddies.  &quot;Train 2 zone!!!&quot; is not appropriate behavior for big boys and girls in big guilds. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gatorivonhinx>Gatori Vonhinx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/24/03 12:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1156.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tactics Tact</span><hr size=1> Happens a lot in HoH too.  Thank god for insta-cast camo.<br>
